      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <indexterm class="- topic/indexterm ">static bypass switch<indexterm class="- topic/indexterm ">static bypass switch
module</indexterm>
         </indexterm>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <fig class="- topic/fig ">
               <image href="../Images/thyristors_120mm_0000116672.svg"
                      scalefit="yes"
                      translate="yes"
                      xml:lang="en"
                      placement="inline"
                      class="- topic/image "/>
            </fig>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The static bypass switch module consists of the following
main parts:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Thyristors (Q401)</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Static bypass switch controller (A401)</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Fan with fan monitoring (E401)</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The static bypass switch module provides the following
functions:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Built-in PSU supplied from bypass mains input</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Dual speed fan supply for the static bypass switch fans (the
fan speed is controlled from the interface board via an input contact)</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Galvanically isolated thyristor drivers for the static bypass
switch</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Snubber RC networks for the static bypass switch thyristors</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Output voltage measurement. If the UPS main controller or the
communication interface becomes inoperable, the board monitors the
system output phase-neutral voltage and independently enables the
static bypass switch if the output is lost</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Communication interface to the UPS controller</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Two signal outputs to indicate the state of the controller</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Configuration</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Different configurations are
possible: 1- or 3-phase output.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The same static bypass switch
module is used for 1-phase output and for 3-phase output power. In
1-phase configurations all three thyristors are turned on and the
input and output terminals are linked together.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The static bypass
switch controller board must be configured for the actual output voltage
and output Phase configuration. This is done by cutting resistors.
Also some Resistors are marked to be cut for "PXP" have to be removed.
The installed board can be used as reference here.</p>
      </section>
